Eastern Province rugby captain Garrick Mattheus is expecting fierce opposition from the Border Bulldogs in a Carling Currie Cup First Division clash at Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium on Saturday. EP’s Elephants are determined to land a killer blow against a wounded Border Bulldogs outfit. In That Weekend Feeling with Daron Mann this week, Mattheus and Bulldogs coach Lumumba Currie speak about the upcoming game. Subscribe for free: iono.fm | Spotify | Pocket Casts | Player.fm | Google Podcasts